= Abstract (English)

This thesis addresses the development of a modular slot car racing track with radio-controlled vehicles. The project's objective is the implementation of an integrated system for control, time measurement, and visualization.

The project consists of three main components: the main control unit and up to five vehicles including controllers. Each component was designed to ensure functionality, user-friendliness, and durability. All race information can be accessed through the app. The charging station provides easy charging of the controllers.

The focus of this work lies on the development of the system architecture, the implementation of wireless communication, reliable time measurement, as well as the integration of a functional user interface and an engaging racing experience.

